&gt; Ive written an HTML JUnit test runner.  Like the text runner, but
&gt; generates HTML.  Obviously, this is implemented by the ANT tasks but,
&gt; since we use a make build, this isnt terribly useful to me.  Its
&gt; prototype code at the moment, but it works.  Ive implemented
&gt; TestListener.  My columns currently include:
&gt;
&gt; - Test name
&gt; - Output (with stderr coloured differently to stdout)
&gt; - Problem (ie. Exception or Assert)
&gt; - Time
&gt; - Memory delta
